Date: Mon, 17 Dec 2001 11:20:04 -0400
From: William C McGrew <mcgrewwc@muohio.edu>
Via: Dale E Reddick <dereddi@hargray.com>

Chimpanzees cooperatively hunt, kill, and eat monkeys and sometimes
bushpigs. When they get duikers [antelope, it is usually [a
solitary [chimp. In all types of meat-eating, sharing occurs, but not
always, i the hunter is alone and stays that way. [Gorilla cannibalism
following infanticide is known from the Virunga population, but that
is the only type of carnivory that I know of from the species.
Regarding the infection chain, it would seem that monkeys are more lik
ely the intermediate host, given that they are more common prey,
closer phylogenetically to apes, and do harbor viruses resembling
HIV2, which is transmissible [by blood.
